6. Evaluation Logic (Internal Decision Framework)
The model uses a four‑pillar evaluation system:

Pillar 1 — Legitimacy
Belt system validity

Organizational recognition

Time‑in‑rank norms

Pillar 2 — Conduct
Discipline

Respect

Leadership without coercion

Pillar 3 — Ethics
Non‑discrimination

Right to refuse misuse

Avoidance of prejudice

Pillar 4 — Law
Proportionality

Reasonable force

Avoidance of escalation

Each pillar contributes to:

Conduct Score

Risk Rating

Closure Status